-- Telefonica Brasil says has not been contacted for TIM joint bid 
-- By Brad Haynes
-- Tue Oct 14, 2014 12:36PM EDT
-- None



SAO PAULO, Oct 14 (Reuters) - Telefonica Brasil SA <VIVT4.SA> said investment banking firm Grupo BTG Pactual <BPAC3.SA> has not reached out to make a joint bid for TIM Participacoes SA <TIMP3.SA> and is instead focusing on integrating GVT SA, the Brazilian telecommunications company it recently bought, Chief Executive Officer Antonio Carlos Valente said on Tuesday.   (Reporting by Brad Haynes; Editing by Chizu Nomiyama)  ((caroline.stauffer@thomsonreuters.com; +55 11 5644 7726; Reuters Messaging: caroline.stauffer.thomsonreuters.com@reuters.net))  Keywords: TIM PARTICIPACOES M&A/TELEFONICABRASIL

